(.venv) christinaward@Christinas-MacBook-Air codestar_blog % git add README.md
fatal: pathspec 'README.md' did not match any files
ChatGPT said:
That error just means Git can’t find a file called README.md in your project folder — so there’s nothing to stage.

Let’s troubleshoot quickly:

1. Check if the file exists
Run:

ls
or (for more detail):

ls -la
This will list everything in your codestar_blog folder. Do you actually see a README.md file there?

2. If it doesn’t exist
You probably haven’t created it yet. To make one:

echo "# codestar_blog" > README.md
Then stage it:

git add README.md
3. If it does exist but has a typo
Maybe the file is called Readme.md or readme.MD. Git is case-sensitive, so double-check the exact spelling and case. Use that name in git add.

4. Confirm staging worked
Run:

git status
You should see README.md under Changes to be committed.

