ChatGPT said:
Ahh yep — that error happens a lot on macOS when trying to install psycopg2. It’s failing because it can’t find pg_config, which is part of PostgreSQL’s developer tools.

You’ve got a couple of options:

🔹 Easiest fix (recommended in development)
Install the binary wheel instead of compiling from source:

pip install psycopg2-binary~=2.9
This package includes prebuilt binaries, so you don’t need PostgreSQL installed locally. For development, it’s perfectly fine.

🔹 Alternative (if you want the full psycopg2)
You’d need to install PostgreSQL client tools so pg_config is available.

On macOS (with Homebrew):

brew install postgresql
Then try again:

pip install psycopg2~=2.9
🔹 Updating your requirements file
Once it installs successfully, update your requirements:

pip freeze > requirements.txt
✅ Most Django projects (especially early on) just use psycopg2-binary to avoid this hassle, and only switch to psycopg2 proper in production.

Do you want me to adjust your install command so it’s a single line that will work right away (with dj-database-url + psycopg2-binary)?

