    "DATABASE_URL",
    "postgresql://neondb_owner:npg_CcFdpU3jsPE4@ep-curly-dew-agty1kbb.c-2.eu-central-1.aws.neon.tech/aids_wasp_thump_969382"
)
Notes:

Remove the < and >; they’re not part of the URL.

Make sure this env.py is imported before your settings try to access DATABASE_URL. For example, in settings.py:

import sys
import os

# Import your env.py first
sys.path.append(os.path.join(BASE_DIR, "path_to_env_py_folder"))
import env  # <-- ensures DATABASE_URL is set

import dj_database_url

DATABASES = {
    "default": dj_database_url.parse(os.environ.get("DATABASE_URL"))
}
