A couple of points to improve your env.py so it works smoothly for Django + Heroku:

1. Add your SECRET_KEY here too
Right now, your settings.py has a hard-coded secret key, which GitGuardian already flagged. You should move it into env.py (for local) and Heroku config vars (for production).

Example:

import os

os.environ.setdefault(
    "DATABASE_URL",
    "postgresql://neondb_owner:your_real_password@ep-curly-dew-agty1kbb.c-2.eu-central-1.aws.neon.tech/aids_wasp_thump_969382"
