# Optional flag to help settings.py switch to local mode
os.environ.setdefault("DEVELOPMENT", "True")
2. Update settings.py to use environment variables
Instead of your current hard-coded secret key:

SECRET_KEY = os.environ.get('SECRET_KEY')
And for debug mode (so Heroku isn’t running in debug):

DEBUG = os.environ.get("DEVELOPMENT") == "True"
3. Git safety
Make sure env.py is in your .gitignore (so it doesn’t leak secrets again).

Double check by running:

git rm --cached env.py
git commit -m "Remove env.py from repo"
git push
(This removes it from Git history going forward — but not from past commits.)

